Definition: disinclined to work or exertion
Example: faineant kings under whose rule the country languished; an indolent hanger-on; too lazy to wash the dishes; shiftless idle youth; slothful employees; the unemployed are not necessarily work-shy
Synonyms: noun, attribute, faineance, indolent, indolence, lazy, laziness, act, otiose, slothful, slothfulness, work-shy, disinclined, to, work, or, exertion, kings, under, whose, rule, the, country, languished, an, hanger-on, too, wash, dishes, shiftless, idle, youth, employees, unemployed, are, not, necessarily
Category: adj.all
